When I draw stuff like musical instruments and guns I go out of my way to make sure that fretboards have the correct number and spacing of frets on them, that pickups have correct number of magnets present (if visible) and that guns have gas tubes, operating rods and charging handles in the correct places (or in places that make sense if I design my own)

Hell, when I design my own planes I make sure that the center of mass and center of lift are (or least appear to be) properly aligned properly and that the main legs of the landing gear are in a position that allows for the aircraft to have a sensible Vr on takeoff.

Jumping back in, don't overthink it. That's how you get tumblrina levels of SJW.
If you've got any worldbuilding, it's actually harder to write YA/SJW dystopias than spread the blame. And if you do dip into the more blatant settings, just hint to the reader that those glorious rebels/egalitarians/socialists also have dark secrets. Maybe worse.
Someone will see it as a shitty allegory. You can't avoid that entirely.
But you can tweak said person's nose in the process, and allow the smarter reader to see deeper into the setting.
